Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:16.760 --> 00:00:22.110
Your doctor has recommended that you have
a lower GI endoscopy. But what does that actually

00:00:22.110 --> 00:00:24.220
mean?

00:00:24.220 --> 00:00:30.230
A lower GI endoscopy is a diagnostic procedure
used by your doctor to inspect the inside

00:00:30.230 --> 00:00:37.230
of your rectum and colon. While it's considered
a surgical procedure, endoscopy does not involve

00:00:37.590 --> 00:00:38.780
an incision.

00:00:38.780 --> 00:00:43.970
Instead, your doctor will pass a flexible
tube, called an endoscope through your anus

00:00:43.970 --> 00:00:47.620
and into your rectum and colon.

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:52.949
This tube has a tiny video camera mounted
on its tip.

00:00:52.949 --> 00:00:56.110
It also contains a small tool used for taking
tissue samples.

00:00:56.110 --> 00:00:59.570
Your doctor can use the endoscope to inspect
the entire lower half of your digestive system.

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:04.920
